# Copy this file to .env (untracked — see .gitignore) and fill in the values.
# config.py loads it at import time; real environment variables take
# precedence over anything set here.

# Personal access token used to publish data/stats.db as the `data-latest`
# GitHub Release asset, by both scripts/publish_db.py and the Data Admin
# page's "Publish data" button. Create a fine-grained token at
# https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new scoped to just the
# repo named in config.GITHUB_REPO, with Repository permissions →
# Contents: Read and write.
#
# Note this is NOT the token the Feedback page uses — that one is a Streamlit
# secret (.streamlit/secrets.toml) needing Issues: write instead. Same name,
# different mechanism; see CLAUDE.md's "Deployment" section.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
